OL,3,CKetamine 'should not' become class A
OL,4,Cdrug, government's expert panel says
OL,6,FPublishing its decision on Wednesday,
OL,7,Fthe ACMD said drug users had explained
OL,8,Fupgrading Ketamine to class A would
OL,9,Fnot reduce its use.
OL,11,FHealth and social care professionals
OL,12,Falso voiced opposition to
OL,13,Freclassification.
OL,15,FChair of the ACMD Professor David Wood
OL,16,Fsaid: "The ACMD report highlights the
OL,17,Fneed for a 'whole system approach'
OL,18,Fthrough its recommendations to tackle
OL,19,Fissues related to ketamine use, as no
OL,20,Fsingle recommendation is sufficient to
OL,21,Fdo this alone."
